{
  "texts": [
    "For example, our course syllabus contains sections on both what the students need to submit, and what happens if a submission is found to be in violation of academic integrity.",
    "When queried with \"what do I need to submit\", the simpler model tended to retrieve document chunks related to both the submission requirements and the submission penalties.",
    "This necessitated the retrieval of more documentsin our case, testing indicated that retrieving 10 document chunks led to a high chance that one of those retrieved chunks contained the answer to the query.",
    "The downside to this being that more chunks retrieved means that the LLM must be provided with longer inputs, which simultaneously increases cost and, as has been shown in [14], can lead to decreased accuracy.",
    "For this reason the number of chunks to retrieve should be adjusted and the system tested before release to students.Finally, the size of the document chunks can affect the overall accuracy of the system."
  ]
}